        <mn>2</mn>
      </msub>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">u_{2}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math>, SLICE proceeds to estimate the likelihood that a pair of genomic loci are indeed interacting. These probabilities represent the likelihood of detecting zero, one, or both loci within a nuclear profile, under the assumption that the loci are *not* interacting:

